namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.
namedLocations.name: ZIP Code

transcript.text: Hello in this video we will learn about new feature Advanced zip codes enhanced in version 7.3.

We have introduced a pattern for the admin to configure a wide variety of zip codes very efficiently and quickly through which along with separated values, the admin will get the option to use wild cards for example at the front store.
Once the customer enters any zip code, then the codes will be searched according to the initial constants and can handle all possible future values.
Now there will be a trash icon given along with every zip code, thus making it easier for the admin to manage and also eradicates the pain of scrolling the zip code list under flat shipping method.
If the shipping setting is zip code based, then admin gets the option to enter the comma separated zip code values and wild card character.
There will be help provided for the same.
For local pickup shipping method in address section, admin will get to enter the wild card formatted zip codes.
They'll also get a help section for the same.
Thanks for your time to watching this video.
